I just updated `react-page-middleware` so if you reclone (and re-npm-install) it should work now, but I just hacked a fix onto it - not sustainable.

I was suggesting that we do:

```
// In ReactVersion.js
module.exports = "0.4";
```

Okay -- I think we were trying to avoid having to specify the version in more places than just `package.json`. Perhaps it makes sense to say

```
if (typeof __VERSION__ !== "undefined") {
  React.version = __VERSION__;
}
```

though I have no idea if the constant folding is smart enough to do something intelligent with that.

I thought about hard coding too and having a part of the build validate it. I'm still game to do that in the short term if it unbreaks things in a better way than you already did.

